<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause xmlns:xt="urn:xpressauthor:trackchanges" id="_5234c962-ded1-4278-8b92-820a4803de16" outputclass="ncc-clause"><meta><facet building="Class 1a"/><facet building="Class 1b"/><facet building="Class 10a"/><facet building="Class 10b"/><facet building="Class 10c"/></meta><sptc>E1D2</sptc><title id="_ed0b4f01-cc66-453e-a581-569bd99fa3c0">Fire hydrants</title><archive-num>2019: E1.3</archive-num><subclause id="_17639f47-d2b7-48e7-a7f6-9f6a66afb20e" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_d14a7ff3-42a7-4422-adbc-5c07cb459359">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>A fire hydrant system must be provided to serve a building—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_1c8aadb0-c2d4-4d53-ab1f-0629ab9c2b6a">having a total <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/2abe2d62-a871-4509-969b-2425466626a4/1314_2.10.0.xml#_7da927fe-453e-424f-b6ec-280f4e464397" id="_f4c20536-e379-4572-91ed-d364383ccd2f" inv:access="external" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">floor area</xref> greater than 500 m<sup xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" id="_8b1f6d6c-bb83-4bc7-8ca6-c9d8d45801a3" inv:access="external">2</sup>; and</li><li id="_ab03178c-05a8-4b9a-92ff-fb419f15e169">where a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/2abe2d62-a871-4509-969b-2425466626a4/1276_2.3.0.xml#_2017565b-5523-4b4c-b656-ae08d7dcdbfd" id="_2233aeec-738e-4dd1-bf57-dd0d734f64f1" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">fire brigade station</xref> is—<ol><li>no more than 50 km from the building as measured along roads; and</li><li>equipped with equipment capable of utilising a fire hydrant.</li></ol></li></ol></subclause><subclause id="_7d9ae74c-2634-4d13-8e63-fb28728dff6d" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_29ad20a1-e49a-4be5-b704-2a1a351367c6">SubClause</title><num>2</num><p>The fire hydrant system must be installed in accordance with—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_ff2cdfc5-dfb9-4a06-8c28-70073eb2472b">AS 2419.1; or</li><li id="_7d1cc8b4-2426-48e5-8170-286866b81692">AS 2118.6, where applicable; or</li><li id="_4b47d112-a468-4de1-83cc-368921929aec">FPAA101H, where applicable.</li></ol></subclause><subclause id="_0681add2-2f05-4b9a-be82-bb666d8bd8da" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_47cff275-1ad6-4f6a-800b-3c7384c7578c">SubClause</title><num>3</num><p>Notwithstanding—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_3d857b6c-bc7f-408a-8134-817af9387e0a">2(a), a Class 8 <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/2abe2d62-a871-4509-969b-2425466626a4/1255_0.4.0.xml#_7a37df1f-0b8b-4b03-94ca-69ea423a363f" id="_232bc3e1-debd-4d72-92c8-8f269012601a" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">electricity network substation</xref> need not comply with clause 4.1.2 of AS 2419.1 if—<ol><li>it cannot be connected to a town main supply; and</li><li>one hour water storage is provided for fire-fighting; and</li></ol></li><li id="_1bc0ee71-fe76-4c5c-bab7-8363040f3d63">2(b), plastic pipes and fittings must not be used above-ground in combined sprinkler and hydrant systems.</li></ol></subclause><subclause id="_1e488705-7501-4d50-a2d0-d7c8af99d38c" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_f9e04f0f-3084-44ef-92b3-07fe0c33232f">SubClause</title><num>4</num><p>Where internal fire hydrants are provided, they must serve only the <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/2abe2d62-a871-4509-969b-2425466626a4/1483_25.0.0.xml#_53ff3ea1-55e7-4f2a-b2b3-ca445ff64c15" id="_7b8e96d6-86ed-4601-b63c-786b964b05fa" inv:access="external" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">storey</xref> on which they are located except that a <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/2abe2d62-a871-4509-969b-2425466626a4/1473_0.4.0.xml#_d2c89488-8a36-464b-94f6-a91d0f5a6c9c" id="_7bc66e61-7304-4072-9095-f42abfca0c49" inv:access="external" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">sole-occupancy unit</xref>—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_9fcc1b13-23f5-4b88-b8c2-568bda08ad82">in a Class 2 or 3 building or Class 4 part of a building may be served by a single fire hydrant located at the level of egress from that <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/2abe2d62-a871-4509-969b-2425466626a4/1473_0.4.0.xml#_d2c89488-8a36-464b-94f6-a91d0f5a6c9c" id="_3f329461-cf1a-4150-8216-6014c7885f61" inv:access="external" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">sole-occupancy unit</xref>; or</li><li id="_92183cfe-7fee-4091-8d23-654c2484b372">of not more than 2 <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/2abe2d62-a871-4509-969b-2425466626a4/1483_25.0.0.xml#_53ff3ea1-55e7-4f2a-b2b3-ca445ff64c15" id="_5988ac9d-2b04-4d4c-aeba-a55a65c6bc89" inv:access="external" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">storeys</xref> in a Class 5, 6, 7, 8 or 9 building may be served by a single fire hydrant located at the level of egress from that <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/2abe2d62-a871-4509-969b-2425466626a4/1473_0.4.0.xml#_d2c89488-8a36-464b-94f6-a91d0f5a6c9c" id="_211a8db4-8cc7-4c7b-9850-a2c8db64a7f7" inv:access="external" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">sole-occupancy unit</xref> provided the fire hydrant can provide coverage to the whole of the <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/2abe2d62-a871-4509-969b-2425466626a4/1473_0.4.0.xml#_d2c89488-8a36-464b-94f6-a91d0f5a6c9c" id="_348daf92-3ce8-486f-bf2b-407803c489ae" inv:access="external" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">sole-occupancy unit</xref>.</li></ol></subclause></clause>